@FOOTNOTE{Note1,key="Note1",note="The Coulomb/HO asymmetry has been refined to four layers across Sprint~5 Track~S5 (gauge-content), Paper~30 (SU(2) Wilson on $S^3$), and Sprint~ST-SU3 (SU(3) Wilson on $S^5$): (i)~spectrum-computing role of $L_0$ (\protect \textbf  {Coulomb-specific}); (ii)~calibration~$\pi $ (\protect \textbf  {Coulomb-specific}); (iii)~Wilson gauge with natural matter coupling (\protect \textbf  {Coulomb-specific}); (iv)~universal Wilson--Hodge combinatorial vocabulary (\protect \textbf  {universal}). Sprint~ST-SU3 split the Wilson layer into ``gauge alone'' (universal) versus ``gauge with natural matter coupling'' (Coulomb-specific): on $S^3$, $S^3 = \protect \mathrm  {SU}(2)$ means the matter spinor lives in the same representation as the Wilson links, and gauge-matter coupling is natural; on $S^5$, the matter representations $(N, 0)$ have dimensions that grow with~$N$, so a uniform link-rep matter coupling is not available, and any coupling reverts to a Clebsch--Gordan intertwiner --- the same obstruction Sprint~5 identified. See \protect \texttt  {debug/st\protect \_su3\protect \_wilson\protect \_memo.md}~\protect \S  ~5.4."}
